# 🔄 CBT Recruitment Pipeline — Full Walkthrough

> **Project:** Convergent Graduate Academy Program (CGAP) Recruitment Portal
> **Last Updated:** 2026-04-30

---

## Step 1 — Application Submission

**Who does it:** The **Candidate** *(public, no login required)*

The candidate fills the application form on the public landing page, uploads their resume (PDF/DOCX), and submits.

**What happens automatically:**
- Candidate record saved to DB with status → `Applied`
- AI screening (Gemini) fires immediately and calculates an `ai_score` and `ai_reasoning`
- 📧 **Email sent to:** Recruitment Team + Approvers → *"[New Application] Candidate Name"*

---

## Step 2 — Application Review & Approval

**Who does it:** `Master` or `Approver`

Opens the **Candidate Pipeline**, reviews the AI score, AI reasoning, and uploaded resume, then takes an action.

| Decision | New Status | Emails Triggered |
|---|---|---|
| **Approve** | `Approved` | 📧 Candidate gets assessment booking link<br>📧 Recruitment Team gets `[Approved]` notice |
| **Reject** | `Rejected` | 📧 Candidate gets professional declination email<br>📧 Recruitment Team gets `[Final Decision: Rejected]` notice |

---

## Step 3 — Assessment Slot Booking

**Who does it:** The **Candidate** *(via their unique booking link)*

The candidate clicks the link from their approval email and self-selects an available time slot for their technical assessment.

**What happens automatically:**
- Slot is atomically locked to that candidate (concurrent booking protected)
- Status updated → `Assessment Scheduled`
- 📧 **Email sent to:** Recruitment Team → *"[Slot Booked] Candidate — Time"*

---

## Step 4 — Assessment Score Upload

**Who does it:** `Master` or `HR`

After the technical assessment is completed, the admin uploads the candidate's score directly from the **Candidate Pipeline** table using the **Upload** button.

- Status moves → `Assessment Completed`
- No email is triggered at this step

---

## Step 5 — L1 Interview Request

**Who does it:** `Master` or `HR`

Admin navigates to the **Interviews** section and triggers an L1 interview broadcast for the candidate.

**What happens automatically:**
- Status moves → `To Be Interviewed`
- 📧 **Email sent to:** All **L1 Interviewers** → Email with ✅ *Available* / ❌ *Not Available* one-click buttons

When an L1 Interviewer responds:
- Their availability is recorded in the database
- 📧 **Email sent to:** Recruitment Team → *"[Response] Candidate — Available/Unavailable + suggested time"*

---

## Step 6 — L1 Interview & Feedback

**Who does it:** `L1_Interviewer`

The interviewer conducts the session and submits structured scores and written feedback through the **Interviews** admin page.

- Status moves → `Interview In Progress`
- The L1 interviewer can optionally **flag the candidate for an L2 interview** at this point

---

## Step 7 *(Optional)* — L2 Interview Request

**Who does it:** `L1_Interviewer` *(requests it)* → `Master` or `HR` *(confirms & broadcasts)*

If the L1 interviewer escalates the candidate:

- 📧 **Email sent to:** All **L2 Interviewers** → Same availability email flow as L1
- L2 Interviewers respond with availability; Recruitment Team is notified of each response

---

## Step 8 — Final Decision

**Who does it:** Interviewers submit feedback → `Master` or `HR` sets the final status

| Decision | Final Status | Emails Triggered |
|---|---|---|
| **Recommend** | [Recommended](file:///d:/Anas/Cbt%20Recruitment%20Portal/src/lib/email.ts#35-54) | 📧 Candidate gets congratulations email<br>📧 Recruitment Team gets `[Final Decision: Recommended]` |
| **Not Recommend** | `Not Recommended` | 📧 Candidate gets declination email<br>📧 Recruitment Team gets `[Final Decision: Not Recommended]` |

---

## 📊 Role vs. Access Matrix

| Action | Master | Approver | HR | L1 Interviewer | L2 Interviewer |
|---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| **View candidates** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Approve / Reject application** | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Edit candidate profile** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Upload assessment score** | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Manage assessment slots** | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Trigger L1 / L2 interview** | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Submit L1 interview feedback** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| **Submit L2 interview feedback** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| **Set final status (Recommended/Not)** | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Delete candidates** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Manage users & roles** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Configure team notifications** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |

---

## 📧 Email Notification Summary

| Trigger | Recipient |
|---|---|
| New application submitted | Recruitment Team + Approvers |
| Candidate approved | Candidate (booking link) + Recruitment Team |
| Candidate rejected (initial) | Candidate (declination) + Recruitment Team |
| Assessment slot booked | Recruitment Team |
| L1 interview triggered | All L1 Interviewers |
| L2 interview triggered | All L2 Interviewers |
| Interviewer responds to availability | Recruitment Team |
| Final decision: Recommended | Candidate (congrats) + Recruitment Team |
| Final decision: Not Recommended | Candidate (declination) + Recruitment Team |

---

> [!NOTE]
> The `recruitment_team`, `approver`, `l1_interviewers`, and `l2_interviewers` notification email lists are configurable from **Portal Settings → Team Notifications**.
